{"detail":{"ID":1189,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-06 16:03:12","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-06 16:03:12","post_content":"The <em>Seunsangga Citywalk<\/em> is here conceived as a spine of infrastructural potential\u00a0that maximizes and encourages variety and intensity in the use of public space. Going beyond circulation and commerce as the main uses of public space, it aspires to recast it as the locus of the unfolding of life\u2019s events for both citizens and visitors. The project is to embrace the essential paradox at the heart of urbanism: knowing next to nothing about the future, we still plan for it.\u00a0What will hold the project together is not spectacular and expensive form with which we would likely be tired of the day after tomorrow. Instead, the project will be realized with the maximum possible freedom of use of spaces held together by an assembly of unique experiences. Furthermore the kit-of-parts approach is also at home in the inspired optimistic madness\u00a0that begot the Seunsangga in the first place. This condition is still blissfully present everywhere in the neighborhood, populated as it is by an infinity of small shops where people earn their living busily making things.","post_title":"<p>Seunsangga Citywalk, Seoul, KR 2015<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"seunsangga-citywalk-seoul-kr-2015","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-06-05 16:20:04","post_modified_gmt":"2017-06-05 16:20:04","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=1189","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","ancestors":[],"page_template":"","post_category":[],"tags_input":[],"extended":{"year":"","images":[{"image":{"width":1500,"height":927,"file":"2017\/04\/OBRA_SEUNSANGGA_01.jpg","sizes":{"thumbnail":{"file":"OBRA_SEUNSANGGA_01-760x460.jpg","width